Paper: hep-th/9906027

Date: 1999-06-03

Title: Seiberg-Witten Theory and Calogero-Moser Systems

Authors: Eric D'Hoker and D.H. Phong

Comments: 24 pages, Plain TeX, Contribution to Proceedings of Workshop on Gauge

Theory and Integrable Models, Kyoto 1999Journal-ref: Prog.Theor.Phys.Suppl. 135 (1999) 75-93

We present a brief account of a series of recent results on twisted anduntwisted elliptic Calogero-Moser systems, and on their fundamental role in theSeiberg-Witten solution of gauge theories with one massive hypermultiplet inthe adjoint representation of an arbitrary gauge algebra G.